    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Reply to user questions hands-free for Multi-Tool Agent (01115)\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nReply to user questions hands-free for Multi-Tool Agent (01115). It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual multi-tool agent is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Required Fields Present? → Classify with AI → Store as Question → Reunite Branches → Fingerprint for Idempotency → Drop Already-Processed Items → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating multi-tool agent in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Groq API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "781ed33c-0795-95fc-e394-6d8c6600926a",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "048d4de8-c2b9-22db-7ab0-5a5659f434be",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "a8bc1327-de8e-dde6-fe19-646a47e64372",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "6f248f73-cb79-72ea-bd12-e5bc6e0e2960",
      "name": "🧹 Data quality"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your multi-tool agent process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
